M|content-strategy|name: community-cnt-str
M|content-strategy|description: Community building, cnt creation, and soc media growth str for fashion/lifestyle brands. Encodes FAN framework, Big Idea rule, viral cnt formulas, Instagram growth tactics, and comedy sho
M|content-strategy|metadata:
M|content-strategy|type: skill
M|content-strategy|version: 1.0
M|content-strategy|agents: [kai-analyst, nate-growth, lena-brand, atlas-art-director, pixel-prd]
M|content-strategy|The X Factor separating Supreme/Nike/Cortez from everyone else is **community** — not product quality, design, or price.
M|content-strategy|**Hard rule:** You cannot build a community around a product. You can ONLY build it around a **Big Idea** (ideology, culture, or lifestyle). The product represents it — it is not it.
M|content-strategy|> Simon Sinek: "People don't buy what you do, they buy why you do it."
M|content-strategy|> Applied: They don't buy the T-shirt. They buy the greater conceptual meaning the brand represents.
M|content-strategy|Limbic brain controls decisions — emotion fires before logic. A fan turns down a logically better cp because of emotional loyalty.
M|content-strategy|Every cnt dec must serve one of these three goals:
M|content-strategy|| Letter | Meaning | What cnt achieves it |
M|content-strategy||--------|---------|--------------------------|
M|content-strategy|| **F** | **Faithful** | Customer turns down cp — emotional brand lock-in |
M|content-strategy|| **A** | **Advocate** | Customer becomes walking billboard — shares, tags, word-of-mouth |
M|content-strategy|| **N** | **Nurtured** | Customer returns drop after drop — repeat buyer loyalty |
M|content-strategy|Business case: If every customer bought 2× instead of 1× → revenue doubles. Community is the mechanism.
M|content-strategy|Before any cnt brief, these must be answered (stored in brand_big_idea):
M|content-strategy|1. **What does your brand name mean?** (etymology, concept, aspiration)
M|content-strategy|2. **Who is the ONE person that best embodies your brand?** (specific — a friend, celebrity, or archetype. Not a demographic.)
M|content-strategy|3. **What about them is aligned with the brand?** (personality traits, values, beliefs, known behaviours)
M|content-strategy|4. **If that person and others gathered, what would they be doing?** (the unifying activity — this is your cnt scenario universe)
M|content-strategy|5. **What is the greater mission beyond the clothing?** (the ideology that outlasts any single product)
M|content-strategy|**Strength test:** If someone can identify your brand without seeing your logo or product — just from the cnt — your Big Idea is strong enough.
M|content-strategy|**Nike example:**
M|content-strategy|1. Greek goddess of victory — sporting challenge and overcoming
M|content-strategy|2. Michael Jordan — disciplined, love of sport, never-give-up attitude
M|content-strategy|3. Gets up early, persistence, does the work on hard days
M|content-strategy|4. Playing basketball, working out, competing together
M|content-strategy|5. Bring inspiration and innovation to every athlete in the world
M|content-strategy|You cannot force virality. You control volume.
M|content-strategy|> Double cnt = double chances at a sale.
M|content-strategy|**6 techniques — more cnt, less time:**
M|content-strategy|**1. Creator Army** — Micro-influencers send clips back to you.
M|content-strategy|DM followers who already post lifestyle cnt in your niche.
M|content-strategy|Win-win message: "Hey, I love your cnt about [X]. I run [brand] focused on [mission]. I'd love to send free clothing in exchange for a couple of videos of you styling them. You can post them too."
M|content-strategy|**2. Repeatable Series** — 2-3 series that run forever. Never invent from scratch.
M|content-strategy|- Founder Vlog: packing orders, checking samples, behind-scenes prep (1-2×/week)
M|content-strategy|- Customer Spotlight: repost a customer wearing brand + ask 2 questions about their life as it relates to the brand message. Their answer = caption story.
M|content-strategy|- Community Event: turn a brand cg into a literal gathering. Film it.
M|content-strategy|**3. Bulk prd** — One shooting day per week. Walk away with a week (or month) of cnt. Plan all references beforehand. 1-2 shots per video max. Same location, same people.
M|content-strategy|**4. Platform Focus** — Quit all platforms except ONE until mastered.
M|content-strategy|- High-price / community brand → Instagram
M|content-strategy|- Low-price / impulse product → TikTok
M|content-strategy|**5. Repurpose** — Same footage, different hook/text = new video to the algorithm. Re-edit clips in different order. Screenshots from cg → carousel posts.
M|content-strategy|**6. Blend Into Life** — Film real moments that match brand lifestyle. Gym → mental health brand. Hiking → outdoors brand. Training ses → running brand. No fake cnt days.
M|content-strategy|1. **Only product posts** — builds brand on sand. Fix: always show people *living* the lifestyle while wearing the product. Message + product together in every post.
M|content-strategy|2. **Niche too broad** ("premium streetwear") — Fix: find top 3 customers' soc accounts, spot common traits via AI pattern match, pick one specific niche.
M|content-strategy|3. **Theme page disconnect** (pure lifestyle cnt + disconnected product drops) — Fix: every post mixes value AND product. Never pure lifestyle without the garment.
M|content-strategy|4. **Only founder's face** — Fix: feature others. Post as a collab (appears on both accounts, doubles reach). Community = multiple faces, not a personal brand.
M|content-strategy|5. **Fashion film shot landscape / no hook** — Fix: film portrait. Start mid-scene. Split one long film into 3 separate videos.
M|content-strategy|6. **Low quality cnt** — Fix: natural light (window behind camera, never behind subject). Less is more — fewer fonts, colors, elements. Hierarchy — subject is always the most prominent thing.
M|content-strategy|7. **Poor product setup** — Fix: 3 L's before every shoot: **Lighting** (natural, no shadows on product), **Location** (background doesn't distract), **Layout** (product laid neatly, you'd be proud to
M|content-strategy|Do NOT post product ads to grow. Post lifestyle/identity cnt.
M|content-strategy|**3-step event framework:**
M|content-strategy|1. Identify someone who embodies the brand (customer avatar or specific friend)
M|content-strategy|2. Ask what they do in their free time
M|content-strategy|3. Pick the activity most related to brand identity AND achievable on small budget → turn it into a literal event, film it
M|content-strategy|**cnt research method:**
M|content-strategy|1. Search **parallel terms** (directly related: "running") + **adjacent terms** (related niche: "marathon training"). Never search "fashion" — makes you look like every other brand.
M|content-strategy|2. Press **Reels filter** on Instagram Explore (Reels reach cold audiences > followers)
M|content-strategy|3. Scroll with intention — note format: what does the video DO structurally? What's the hook mechanism?
M|content-strategy|4. Apply **Virgil Abloh 3% Rule** — change ONE element by ~3%. Same familiar format, fresh for your brand. Never copy wholesale.
M|content-strategy|**Trial Reels A/B testing:**
M|content-strategy|- Create 5-10 versions of the same video, changing only ONE element (spoken hook, opening frame, or duration)
M|content-strategy|- Post all trials simultaneously — only reaches non-followers, won't appear on grid
M|content-strategy|- After 3-5 days, pick winner to post publicly to grid
M|content-strategy|- Every video gets its best possible chance before the audience sees it
M|content-strategy|Highest-performing format for clothing brands on Instagram Reels. Lifestyle-focused, highly exaggerated, ≤60 seconds. Acts as scroll-stopper + brand ad simultaneously.
M|content-strategy|**Step 1 — Clarify Branding**
M|content-strategy|What is the lifestyle, belief, or ideology behind the brand?
M|content-strategy|- Ideological: mental health brand — belief system
M|content-strategy|- Lifestyle: skateboarding brand — specific activity
M|content-strategy|- Hybrid: self-improvement — ideology + lifestyle traits
M|content-strategy|**Step 2 — Pick a Scenario (least obvious)**
M|content-strategy|> Football brand: don't pick "on the pitch" → pick "locker room before game" or "setting out shoes at home the night before"
M|content-strategy|Least obvious = most original story. Keep it accessible: no skyscrapers or locations you can't access.
M|content-strategy|**Step 3 — Create a Character**
M|content-strategy|Your target customer. Exaggerate their traits: extremely good, bad, or ordinary at something.
M|content-strategy|- Goals must align with brand identity (winning brand → character's goal = win)
M|content-strategy|- Conflict must directly oppose the goal
M|content-strategy|**Step 4 — Infuse Conflict**
M|content-strategy|- Visually obvious (audience understands without narration)
M|content-strategy|- Comical, not serious — serious risks cringe. Exaggeration + irony = cool.
M|content-strategy|- Character juxtaposition — audience expects X, character is surprisingly Y
M|content-strategy|**Step 5 — Structure for soc Media**
M|content-strategy|| Element | Rule |
M|content-strategy||---------|------|
M|content-strategy|| Hook | Start mid-scene. No orientation or character introductions. First frame = action or curiosity already happening. |
M|content-strategy|| Curiosity Gap | Raise questions without answering them (who? where? why?). Audience stays to find out. |
M|content-strategy|| Payoff | Unexpected twist in final 3-5 seconds. Rewards the viewer for watching. Makes them rewatch or share. |
M|content-strategy|| Tagline | 2-4 word brand punchline at end. Summarises entire ideology. e.g. "Take what's yours." |
M|content-strategy|| No-Sound Test | Watch without audio — story must still make sense. Nearly half of Instagram users watch silent. Zero or minimal dialogue preferred. |
M|content-strategy|| Platform | Caption length | Format | Primary goal |
M|content-strategy||---------|---------------|--------|-------------|
M|content-strategy|| Instagram | 1-2 lines + hashtags | Portrait Reels, carousels | Loyal community, saves |
M|content-strategy|| Facebook | 3-5 lines + question CTA | Video, link posts | Community groups, shares |
M|content-strategy|| Threads | Under 280 chars | Raw thoughts, hot takes | Conversation, relatability |
M|content-strategy|| TikTok | 1 line | Vertical video | Discovery, impulse |
M|content-strategy|Before any cnt suggestion or brief is finalised:
M|content-strategy|- [ ] 3 L's passed — Lighting (natural), Location (non-distracting), Layout (product neat + intentional)
M|content-strategy|- [ ] No-sound test — story lands without audio
M|content-strategy|- [ ] FAN goal assigned — this piece serves Faithful / Advocate / or Nurtured
M|content-strategy|- [ ] Big Idea aligned — reinforces brand ideology, not just shows product
M|content-strategy|- [ ] System 1 score ≥ 3 — makes someone feel something in 2 seconds
M|content-strategy|- [ ] People in frame — at least one human wearing/using the product (no empty landscapes with quote overlays)
M|content-strategy|- [ ] Platform native — format matches the platform it's being posted to